# inspector_param_reset.scn — 活體牙 (Tier2): Inspector parameter reset + default/override text
# color + jog-dial (DragFloat) edit. = TiXL InputValueUi (ContextMenuForItem "Reset to default" /
# ResetInputToDefault + the IsDefault? TextMuted : ForegroundFull value-text color, line 516, and
# the SingleValueEdit drag-to-scrub editor ported here as imgui DragFloat).
#
# On RadialPoints (node:1) inside EmitterComp, its scalar Float param RadiusOffset (starts default):
#   1. JOG-DIAL drag the param -> an instance override materializes (DragFloat edit writes it live).
#      Now drawn ForegroundFull white (capture overridden).
#   2. Right-click param -> "Reset to default" item present (TiXL only shows it when !IsDefault);
#      click it -> the override is ERASED (definition default shines through). Undoable.
#   3. After reset the value text is drawn TextMuted grey -> the screenshot DIFFERS from (1)
#      (the color difference is on-screen and load-bearing).
#   4. Cmd+Z restores the override (live-app undo round-trip of the reset command).
#
# RED proofs:
#   - (1) change the override "any" check to "all(.==false)" -> FAIL (the drag really overrode it).
#   - (2) change the erase "all(.==false)" to "any" -> FAIL (reset really erased the override).
#   - (3) change assert_diff to assert_same -> FAIL (override->default flips the text color).
#   - (4) change the restore "any" to "all(.==false)" -> FAIL (Cmd+Z really brought it back).

open app/testdata/compound_smoke.swproj

# Enter EmitterComp (node:1 in Root) and select RadialPoints (node:1 inside). (Same select gesture
# as d4_vec_channels.scn: double to enter, click the inside node title to select it.)
do double @node:1^
assert_state '(.compositionPath | length) == 1'
do click @node:1^
# Baseline: RadiusOffset is at its definition default (no override) -> drawn TextMuted grey.
assert_state '[.lib.symbols[] | select(.id=="EmitterComp") | .children[] | select(.id==1) | .overrides | has("RadiusOffset")] | all(. == false)'
echo radiusoffset-starts-default-grey

# 1. JOG-DIAL: drag the RadiusOffset DragFloat right -> an instance override materializes (white).
# (The drag also forces a fresh inspector-drawn map shot, so @param:RadiusOffset resolves.)
do drag @param:RadiusOffset +60 +0
wait 0.4
assert_state '[.lib.symbols[] | select(.id=="EmitterComp") | .children[] | select(.id==1) | .overrides | has("RadiusOffset")] | any'
capture full overridden
echo jogdial-drag-created-override-white-captured

# 2. Right-click the param -> the TiXL "Reset to default" item renders (eye marker insp:reset);
# click it.
do rclick @param:RadiusOffset
wait 0.4
assert_map_has insp:reset
do click @insp:reset
wait 0.4
# Override ERASED -> the definition default shines through (no key in the serialized overrides).
assert_state '[.lib.symbols[] | select(.id=="EmitterComp") | .children[] | select(.id==1) | .overrides | has("RadiusOffset")] | all(. == false)'
echo reset-erased-the-override

# 3. Now drawn TextMuted grey -> the full-window shot differs from the overridden (white) one.
capture full reset
assert_diff overridden
echo default-vs-override-color-differs-onscreen

# 4. Cmd+Z restores the override (live-app undo round-trip). Click the node title to give the canvas
# focus (Cmd+Z is gated on canvas IsWindowFocused), then Cmd+Z.
do click @node:1^
wait 0.3
do keychord cmd z
wait 0.4
assert_state '[.lib.symbols[] | select(.id=="EmitterComp") | .children[] | select(.id==1) | .overrides | has("RadiusOffset")] | any'
echo undo-restored-the-override
